text: From Professor Strauss' notes, we know who attended the first NASPA Conference. The @NASPAtweets conference has grown from these 6 professionals to almost 8,000 at #NASPA18. #NASPA100 https://t.co/F9fdo7bcwl
Professor Strauss was the first Jewish faculty member at the @umich. #NASPA100

NASPA (then called the Conference of Deans and Advisors of Men) met for the first time on January 24-25, 1919. Six professionals attended this inaugural meeting and the notes were prepared by Professor Louis A. Strauss of the University of Michigan. #NASPA100 https://t.co/GiZhstuFbl

Professor Strauss was a graduate of the Univ. of Michigan and worked his entire life at @UMich. He was a professor of English and Chair of the English Department. He also served on the Committee of Student Affairs, andâ€¨ the Board in Control of Student Publications. #NASPA100

Curious what music sounded like over the decades since @NASPAtweets' founding? The 100th Anniversary Committee curated a list of songs over the past 100 years, accessible via @Spotify https://t.co/DuqIZoUkZZ #NASPA100

@frostburgstate Dr. Manicur was honored by @NASPAgives for her lifetime of commitment to the field with the John L. Blackburn Distinguished Pillar of the Profession Award at #NASPA15 in New Orleans. The @naspa_women Alice Manicur Symposium is named in her honor (2/2). #NASPA100 #Manicur18

A legend in her time, Dr. Alice R. Manicur was a pioneer in student affairs and higher ed who broke the glass ceiling for women in the field. Dr. Manicur was the first female elected as NASPA President in 1976 and concluded her 46 year tenure at @frostburgstate (1/2). #NASPA100 https://t.co/8mfOgAk9nn

The Conference of Deans and Advisers of Men (CDAM) was founded in 1919, renamed the National Association of Deans and Advisers of Men (NADAM) in 1929, and ultimately renamed again in 1951 to become the National Association of Student Personnel Administrators (NASPA). #NASPA100 https://t.co/Q6YLl2YvNT

Did you know the 1930 NASPA Annual Conference was called the "Strawberry Conference"? Dean Ripley promised to "provide all the strawberries you can eat" for Annual Conference participants at the University of Arkansas. #NASPA100 https://t.co/fq8csRJ4yy
